    {
        // ── Overview (Article) ───────────────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Events Overview",
            Slug = "events-overview",
            Summary = "What events are, the four event types, inviting people and tracking who attends, required events, and automatic reminders.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 4,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 1,
            AppRoutes = """["/admin/events"]""",
            Tags = """["events","admin","meetings","training","safety"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Events Overview\n\nUse Events to plan and keep track of everything happening across your shop — team meetings, training sessions, safety briefings, and company get-togethers. You'll find it under Admin > Events. It gives you one place to schedule what's coming up and see who's expected to be there.\n\n### Event Types\n\nEvery event is one of four types:\n- **Meeting** — team meetings, project reviews, stand-ups, and one-on-ones.\n- **Training** — skills training, onboarding, and certification prep.\n- **Safety** — safety briefings, emergency drills, and compliance reviews.\n- **Other** — company socials, announcements, facility tours, or anything else.\n\nEach type has its own icon in the list, so you can spot the kind of event at a glance and filter down to just one kind.\n\n### Inviting People\n\nWhen you create or edit an event, you pick who should come from your active employees. Everyone you add gets a notification inviting them, so the whole crew knows it's on the calendar without you sending a separate email.\n\nEach person you invite carries a status, so you can see where they stand:\n- **Invited** — added to the event, no answer yet\n- **Accepted** — they've confirmed they'll be there\n- **Declined** — they can't make it\n- **Attended** — they showed up (your proof for the record)\n\nThe list shows a headcount for each event, so you can see how many people you've invited at a glance.\n\n### Required vs Optional Events\n\nMark an event Required when attendance isn't a choice — a safety briefing or mandatory compliance training. A required event stands out more strongly in each person's notifications and shows a yellow Required label in the list, so nobody mistakes it for optional. Everything else stays plain.\n\n### Automatic Reminders\n\nEveryone you invite gets a reminder shortly before the event starts. That way people show up on time even if the original invite slipped their mind — you don't have to chase anyone down.\n\n### Where Events Show Up\n\n- **Admin > Events** — where you create, edit, filter, and cancel events\n- **Shop Floor Display** — upcoming events appear on the floor screen, so operators see what's scheduled without leaving their station\n- **Employee Profile** — each person's profile has an Events tab listing the events they're invited to and whether they attended, handy when you're reviewing someone's training history\n\n### Cancelling an Event\n\nCancelling takes an event off the calendar but doesn't erase it — the record stays, so you keep an accurate history of what was scheduled. Everyone invited is told it's off.\n\n### When to Reach for Events\n\n- Scheduling a team meeting or project review\n- Calling a mandatory safety briefing or emergency drill\n- Planning training for new hires or skill-building\n- Keeping a record of who attended which safety training for compliance\n- Announcing a company-wide gathering or social","sections":[]}"""
        });

